                                        </div>
                                        <div class=3D"td-page-content tagdi=
v-type">
                                        <p>The average price for a pound of=
 coffee was $9.139 in September, compared to $8.872 in August, for a 3% inc=
rease, according to data released October 24, 2025 by the U.S. Labor Depart=
ment=E2=80=99s Bureau of Labor Statistics (<a href=3D"https://www.bls.gov/c=
pi/">BLS</a>).</p>
<p>Over a longer period and averaging the BLS=E2=80=99s monthly pricing dat=
a, the per-pound cost went up to $6.322 in 2024 from $6.16 in 2023, registe=
ring a year-over-year increase of 2.6%. (One pound of coffee can make about=
 48 6-ounce cups of coffee.)</p>
<p>Coffee is extremely popular. <a href=3D"https://www.britishcoffeeassocia=
tion.org/coffee-in-the-uk/coffee-facts" title=3D"Coffee is the most popular=
 drink worldwide with around two billion cups consumed every day">The Briti=
sh Coffee Association reports</a> that it is the most sought drink worldwid=
e with around 2 billion cups consumed daily. About 66% of American drink co=
ffee every day, <a href=3D"https://www.bevindustry.com/articles/94880-coffe=
e-consumption-hits-two-decade-high-nca-poll-shows" title=3D"Coffee consumpt=
ion hits two-decade high, NCA poll shows">according to&nbsp;polling</a> rel=
eased by the National Coffee Association (NCA).</p>
<div style=3D"margin-left:-30px"><iframe width=3D"800" height=3D"560" seaml=
ess=3D"" frameborder=3D"0" scrolling=3D"yes" src=3D"cid:frame-B51FE2BA61F3A=
1D66E8603A5A1E86035@mhtml.blink"></iframe></div>
<p>As shown in the table below, the cost of coffee peaked in 2012. Prices h=
ave been teetering lower since that height. The first column in the table l=
ists average annual prices for a pound of coffee and the last column shows =
those prices adjusted for inflation in 2022 dollars.</p>
